<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Rightful" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Rightful,</orth> 1) just: <cit><quote>no r. plea might plead for justice there,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1649" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1649</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>most r. judge,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.301" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. IV, 1, 301</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>whose r. cause prevails,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.1.205" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 1, 205</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) lawful, legitimate: <cit><quote>for the deposing of a r. king,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 5.1.50" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 1, 50</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to put forth my r. hand in a well-hallowed cause,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.293" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 293</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to plant the r. heir,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.5.80" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 5, 80</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.1.60" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.3.30" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 3, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.3.30" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 3, 30</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.2.24" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.2.24" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 24</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.2.139" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 139</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.178" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 178</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>